				<div class="content">I am so excited to see all the progress in this thread.<br>
<br>
Simon,<br>
<br>
Yes the ringing can only be coming from the speaker, so that's a good sign. Considering you got that far I know you have a SIM card installed and activated, so that's also good.<br>
<br>
I made more improvements to the firmware before sending out the batches everyone received* and now calls are answered by pressing the top-right "hook" button only (not too at a time). I attempted to capture all of the operational functionality with this one image from the build page: <a href="http://skysedge.us/unsmartphones/rotarycellphone_3g/build/functionguide_top.JPG" class="postlink">http://skysedge.us/unsmartphones/rotary ... de_top.JPG</a> But that's probably not enough information. Long story short, answer (and place) calls just by pressing the hook button once and not two buttons at the same time as I think I described in the video. <br>
<br>
I'm thinking your next step should be trying to pick up the incoming call. Once that's working and the person on the other end hears you, the phone <em class="text-italics">should</em> be fully functional. It *shouldn't* matter but can you attempt to answer the incoming call with the mode switch in each of the three positions?<br>
<br>
~Justine</div>
