				<h3>Re: So far...</h3>
				<div class="date">Posted: <strong>Sun Apr 26, 2020 1:00 am</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>SteveC</strong></div>
				<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1748">paedipod</a> wrote: <a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1523#p1523" data-post-id="1523" onclick="if(document.getElementById(hash.substr(1)))href=hash">↑</a><div class="responsive-hide">Sat Apr 25, 2020 11:07 pm</div></cite>
I am waiting for a cable/adapter for the AVRISP so I can re-flash the firmware if that is the issue. 
</div></blockquote>

Good news, no need to wait for your AVR-ISP programmer. You only need a USB cable since Justine supplied the board ready programmed (with bootloader I assume).<br>
<br>
Simply connect the phone to your computer by USB. In the Arduino IDE click Tools --&gt; Port and make sure the USB port is selected, then click ctrl-U to upload via USB (or the right arrow symbol in the toolbar).</div>
			</div>
