				<h3>Re: So far...</h3>
				<div class="date">Posted: <strong>Sun Apr 26, 2020 9:59 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>SteveC</strong></div>
				<div class="content">The confusion is understandable.<br>
<br>
On the 3G phone's main page: "<em class="text-italics">An in-system programmer is required to upload Arduino sketches, as I didn't include a reset line from the UART pins.</em>"<br>
<br>
But this is not the case (from the February 2020 version at least).
<div class="inline-attachment">
			
		
				<dl class="file">
			<dt class="attach-image"><img src="./download/file.php?id=13" class="postimage" alt="reset.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt>
						<dd>reset.jpg (30.1 KiB) Viewed 3344 times</dd>
		</dl>
		
		
			</div>
There is a reset line from the UART. Provided the bootloader has been loaded, the phone's firmware CAN be uploaded via USB. I use this method.<br>
<br>
If it's not working for you (and you're sure the bootloader is OK) check that C10 is installed (just below and to the left of U1).</div>
			</div>
